<paper id="1978358700"><title>A note on reliable full-duplex transmission over half-duplex links</title><year>1969</year><authors><author org="National Physical Lab., Teddington, England" id="2148842653">K. A. Bartlett</author><author org="National Physical Lab., Teddington, England" id="2018551740">R. A. Scantlebury</author><author org="National Physical Lab., Teddington, England" id="2120657151">P. T. Wilkinson</author></authors><n_citation>401</n_citation><doc_type>Journal</doc_type><references><reference>33773470</reference><reference>1981861428</reference><reference>2153580689</reference></references><venue id="103482838" type="J">Communications of The ACM</venue><doi>10.1145/362946.362970</doi><keywords><keyword weight="0.40768">Transmission (mechanics)</keyword><keyword weight="0.4114">Telecommunications</keyword><keyword weight="0.56163">Data transmission</keyword><keyword weight="0.43642">Alternating bit protocol</keyword><keyword weight="0.42707">Computer science</keyword><keyword weight="0.41881">Theoretical computer science</keyword><keyword weight="0.43774">Electronic engineering</keyword><keyword weight="0.49301">Error detection and correction</keyword><keyword weight="0.5768">Duplex (telecommunications)</keyword></keywords><publisher>ACM</publisher><abstract>A simple procedure for achieving reliable full-duplex transmission over half-duplex links is proposed. The scheme is compared with another of the same type, which has recently been described in the literature. Finally, some comments are made on another group of related transmission procedures which have been shown to be unreliable under some circumstances.</abstract></paper>